'''Pete Fry''' is a Canadian politician and business owner in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], who was elected to [[Vancouver City Council]] in the [[Vancouver municipal election, 2018|2018 municipal election]].<ref>[https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/vancouver-municipal-election-2018-1.4841328 "Kennedy Stewart elected mayor of Vancouver"]. [[CBC News]] Vancouver, October 20, 2018.</ref> He is a member of the [[Green Party of Vancouver]].
Fry first ran for city council in the 2014 municipal election, but was not elected.<ref>[https://globalnews.ca/news/1671925/vancouver-election-results-2014-full-results-for-mayor-council-school-and-park-board/ "Vancouver election 2014: Full results for mayor, council, school and park board"]. [[CHAN-DT|Global News BC]], November 16, 2014.</ref> He then secured the nomination of the [[Green Party of British Columbia]] in a 2016 provincial by-election in the riding of [[Vancouver-Mount Pleasant]].<ref>[https://thetyee.ca/News/2016/01/18/Byelection-Vancouver-Mount-Pleasant/ "Byelection Battle: Meet Candidates Vying for Vancouver Mount-Pleasant"]. ''[[The Tyee]]'', January 18, 2016.</ref> In 2017, he ran for Vancouver City Council a second time, in the by-election following the resignation of [[Geoff Meggs]].<ref>[https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/pete-fry-to-run-for-green-party-of-vancouver-in-city-by-election-1.4250951 "Pete Fry to run for Green Party of Vancouver in city by-election"]. [[CBC News]] Vancouver, August 17, 2017.</ref>
Fry owns a graphics and communications agency in Vancouver. His mother is [[Hedy Fry]], the federal Member of Parliament for [[Vancouver Centre]].<ref>[https://www.straight.com/news/347001/pete-fry-better-city-together "Pete Fry: A better city together"]. ''[[The Georgia Straight]]'', October 29, 2014.</ref>
